```julia
function keep_only_names(words::Vector{String})
    return filter(word -> word[1] == uppercasefirst(word), words)
end
```

This function uses `filter` to iterate over the list of strings (`words`) and keeps only those strings where the first letter is equal to the uppercased version of that letter. The `uppercasefirst` function is used to ensure that we are comparing apples-to-apples with the input string, regardless of whether it already starts with a capital letter or not.
